<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 31 at 1:01AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of eastern Lipscomb and
northeastern Hemphill Counties through 130 AM CDT...
At 101 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of Lipscomb, moving southeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lipscomb and Higgins.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
